th the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotationView","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"title":"MapLibre","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","role":"col